---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="5 Signs You Need Sliding Door Replacement in Fort Lauderdale"
  description="Not sure if your sliding door needs replacement? Here are 5 telltale signs it is time to upgrade your sliding door in Fort Lauderdale and South Florida."
  keywords="sliding door replacement, replace sliding door, Fort Lauderdale sliding door, when to replace sliding door, sliding door upgrade"
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-6">5 Signs You Need Sliding Door Replacement in Fort Lauderdale</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 mb-8">Published March 2025 | Top Notch Doors & Windows</p>

    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Sliding doors are one of the most used features in any South Florida home. They connect living spaces to patios, pools, and outdoor areas, making them essential for everyday life. But over time, wear and weather take their toll. Here are five signs that it might be time for a <a href="/services/sliding-door-replacement" class="text-primary hover:underline">sliding door replacement</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">1. The Door Is Extremely Difficult to Open or Close</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      If you are struggling to slide your door open every time, it is a sign of serious underlying issues. While a simple <a href="/services/sliding-door-repair" class="text-primary hover:underline">roller or track repair</a> may help, doors that continue to jam or grind after repair likely have warped frames or structural damage that make replacement the better option.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">2. You Feel Drafts or Notice Moisture Between Panes</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Drafts around your sliding door mean the seals have failed, letting conditioned air escape and humid outdoor air in. In South Florida, this leads to higher energy bills and potential moisture problems. Foggy or condensation-filled glass panels indicate a broken seal in double-pane units, which typically requires full replacement.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">3. The Frame Is Visibly Damaged or Warped</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Florida's heat, humidity, and salt air are tough on door frames. If you notice cracks, warping, rot, or corrosion in the frame, repairs will only be a temporary fix. A new door with a modern, weather-resistant frame will perform better and last longer in the South Florida climate.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">4. The Lock No Longer Engages Properly</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      A sliding door that does not lock securely is a safety concern. While lock hardware can often be replaced, if the door itself has shifted in its frame to the point where the lock cannot align, the entire door assembly may need replacing. Do not compromise on security for your family and property.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">5. Your Door Is Over 15 to 20 Years Old</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Even well-maintained sliding doors have a lifespan. If your door is approaching 15 to 20 years, newer models offer significantly better energy efficiency, security, and storm resistance. Upgrading to a modern <a href="/services/sliding-door-installation" class="text-primary hover:underline">sliding door installation</a> can improve your home's value and reduce your monthly energy costs.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">What to Do Next</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      If you recognize any of these signs, schedule a free inspection with a local door specialist. A professional can tell you whether a repair will extend your door's life or if a full replacement is the smarter investment. At Top Notch Doors & Windows, we provide honest assessments and competitive pricing on every job.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 bg-primary/5 p-8 rounded-lg">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">Need Sliding Door Replacement?</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Contact Top Notch Doors & Windows for a free estimate on sliding door replacement in Fort Lauderdale and across South Florida.</p>
      <a href="/contact-us" class="inline-flex bg-primary text-white px-6 py-3 rounded hover:bg-black transition-colors">Get Your Free Estimate</a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 text-sm text-gray-500">
      <p>Related: <a href="/services/sliding-door-repair" class="text-primary hover:underline">Sliding Door Repair</a> | <a href="/blog/how-much-does-sliding-door-repair-cost-fort-lauderdale" class="text-primary hover:underline">Sliding Door Repair Costs</a> | <a href="/contact-us" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contact Us</a></p>
    </div>
  </article>

